<h3> Frequency Curve </h3>

<div class="solution">
<b>Given Data:</b>

<table border="1" cellpadding="6">
<tr><th>Class Interval</th><th>Frequency</th></tr>
<tr><td>0–10</td><td>4</td></tr>
<tr><td>10–20</td><td>7</td></tr>
<tr><td>20–30</td><td>12</td></tr>
<tr><td>30–40</td><td>5</td></tr>
</table>

<br>
<b>Step 1:</b> Find mid-points of each class interval  
<br>0–10 → 5  
<br>10–20 → 15  
<br>20–30 → 25  
<br>30–40 → 35  

<br><br>
<b>Step 2:</b> Draw X-axis for mid-points and Y-axis for frequencies  
<br>
<b>Step 3:</b> Plot the points (5,4), (15,7), (25,12), (35,5)

<br><br>
<b>Step 4:</b> Join the plotted points smoothly to form frequency curve

<br><br>


</div>

