<h3> Ogive (Cumulative Frequency Curve)</h3>

<b>Given Data:</b>

<table border="1" cellpadding="6">
<tr><th>Class Interval</th><th>Frequency</th></tr>
<tr><td>0–10</td><td>4</td></tr>
<tr><td>10–20</td><td>7</td></tr>
<tr><td>20–30</td><td>12</td></tr>
<tr><td>30–40</td><td>5</td></tr>
</table>

<br>
<b>Step 1: Form cumulative frequency table</b>

<table border="1" cellpadding="6">
<tr><th>Upper Class Boundary</th><th>Cumulative Frequency</th></tr>
<tr><td>10</td><td>4</td></tr>
<tr><td>20</td><td>11</td></tr>
<tr><td>30</td><td>23</td></tr>
<tr><td>40</td><td>28</td></tr>
</table>

<br>
<b>Step 2:</b> Draw X-axis for class boundary and Y-axis for cumulative frequency  
<br>
<b>Step 3:</b> Plot points: (10,4), (20,11), (30,23), (40,28)  
<br>
<b>Step 4:</b> Join points smoothly to obtain ogive

<br><br>
<b>Use:</b>  
Median, quartiles and percentiles can be found from ogive.
</div>

