<h3> Box Plot </h3>

<div class="solution">
<b>Given Data:</b>  
12, 15, 18, 20, 25, 30, 35, 40

<br><br>
<b>Step 1: Arrange the data</b><br>
12, 15, 18, 20, 25, 30, 35, 40

<br><br>
<b>Step 2: Find Median (Q2)</b><br>
Number of observations = 8 (even)<br>
Median = (4th + 5th) / 2 = (20 + 25) / 2 = <b>22.5</b>

<br><br>
<b>Step 3: Find First Quartile (Q1)</b><br>
Lower half: 12, 15, 18, 20<br>
Q1 = (15 + 18) / 2 = <b>16.5</b>

<br><br>
<b>Step 4: Find Third Quartile (Q3)</b><br>
Upper half: 25, 30, 35, 40<br>
Q3 = (30 + 35) / 2 = <b>32.5</b>

<br><br>
<b>Step 5: Identify minimum and maximum values</b><br>
Minimum = 12, Maximum = 40

<br><br>

Five number summary = (12, 16.5, 22.5, 32.5, 40)
</div>

